docs.abstract: What the revamped board has planned for CBS depends on how it views media mergers and what its relationship will be with its controlling shareholder, Shari Redstone.
docs.snippet: What the revamped board has planned for CBS depends on how it views media mergers and what its relationship will be with its controlling shareholder, Shari Redstone.
docs.lead_paragraph: The crisis at the CBS Corporation over the last few months has featured enough drama to make the prime-time shows that will air on its network’s new season in two weeks seem bloodless: multiple allegations of sexual assault against its chief executive published in a prominent magazine, a nasty legal showdown with its controlling shareholder and claims by that shareholder that she was physically bullied by a board member.

headline.main: CBS Board Tries to Move Past Moonves Crisis With New Directors
headline.print_headline: CBS Board Tries to Move Past a Panoply of Crises by Installing New Directors

docs.abstract: A start-up uses visual tracking and behavioral data to operate a new San Francisco market, which lets shoppers walk out unimpeded. And sometimes mischarged.
docs.snippet: A start-up uses visual tracking and behavioral data to operate a new San Francisco market, which lets shoppers walk out unimpeded. And sometimes mischarged.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — One recent afternoon, the city’s newest grocery market was trying to figure out whether I would buy, steal or leave behind a bag of white Cheddar popcorn — and so was I.

headline.main: Stealing From a Cashierless Store (Without You, or the Cameras, Knowing It)

docs.abstract: Many websites offer services to create estate plans for little or no money. Some offer a lawyer to talk to free of charge.

docs.abstract: Not content to merely revive E-Types to their former glory, Jaguar will retrofit them as fully electric machines, but it will be costly: $375,000 or more if you don’t supply the car.
docs.snippet: Not content to merely revive E-Types to their former glory, Jaguar will retrofit them as fully electric machines, but it will be costly: $375,000 or more if you don’t supply the car.
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTEREY, Calif. — No less an authority on the subject of breathtaking automobiles than Enzo Ferrari described Jaguar’s E-Type after its debut at the 1961 Geneva Motor Show as the most beautiful car in the world. Almost 60 years later, that assessment still rings true.

headline.main: Jaguar’s Electric E-Type Marries ’60s Sex Appeal and Tomorrow’s Tech

docs.abstract: Picking a chief financial officer is crucial for Uber because the company has said it plans to go public by the end of 2019, in what is likely to be one of the biggest-ever technology I.P.O.s.
docs.snippet: Picking a chief financial officer is crucial for Uber because the company has said it plans to go public by the end of 2019, in what is likely to be one of the biggest-ever technology I.P.O.s.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — After a yearslong search, Uber has finally found a chief financial officer as it advances toward an initial public offering.

headline.main: Uber Appoints New Head of Finance as It Marches Toward an I.P.O.
headline.print_headline: I.P.O. Nears, And Uber  Hires Head Of Finance

docs.abstract: In a rare sign of internal dissent, more than 100 employees have formed a group to agitate for better representation of conservative views.
docs.snippet: In a rare sign of internal dissent, more than 100 employees have formed a group to agitate for better representation of conservative views.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The post went up quietly on Facebook’s internal message board last week. Titled “We Have a Problem With Political Diversity,” it quickly took off inside the social network.

headline.main: Dozens at Facebook Unite to Challenge Its ‘Intolerant’ Liberal Culture
headline.print_headline: At Facebook,  Workers Cite Intolerance By Liberals

docs.abstract: A year after the Equifax security breach, most people have not frozen their credit records. Consumer advocates recommend freezes to foil identity theft.
docs.snippet: A year after the Equifax security breach, most people have not frozen their credit records. Consumer advocates recommend freezes to foil identity theft.
docs.lead_paragraph: Consumers will soon be able to freeze their credit files without charge. So if you have not yet frozen your files — a recommended step to foil identity theft — now is a good time to take action, consumer advocates say.

headline.main: Freezing Credit Will Now Be Free. Here’s Why You Should Go for It.
headline.print_headline: New Law Makes Freezing Credit Files Free

docs.abstract: The fight will be settled by an auction this weekend. We work out the possibilities.
docs.snippet: The fight will be settled by an auction this weekend. We work out the possibilities.
docs.lead_paragraph: Control of a $30 billion company doesn’t often come down to an auction. But that is the fate of the British broadcaster Sky, one of Europe’s most valuable television businesses.

headline.main: Comcast and Disney (Fox) Battle Again. This Time for British Broadcaster Sky.

docs.abstract: The faster speeds and larger screen sound boring on paper. But an electrical heart sensor gives a glimpse of the promise to come, our reviewer writes.
docs.snippet: The faster speeds and larger screen sound boring on paper. But an electrical heart sensor gives a glimpse of the promise to come, our reviewer writes.
docs.lead_paragraph: A few days ago, I sat in a medical recliner at the University of California, San Francisco. A cardiologist placed 10 stickerlike electrodes onto my limbs and chest and then connected the wires to a dated-looking contraption with a screen and a keyboard on a cart.

headline.main: Apple Watch Series 4 Review: A Big Step for Wearable Gadgets
headline.print_headline: The Apple Watch started as a fitness tracker, but it’s evolving into a health-monitoring device.
